In this statement, President Obama extends his greetings to Muslims in the United States and around the world on the occasion of Eid-ul-Fitr, which marks the end of Ramadan. He acknowledges that Eid is a time of celebration, but also emphasizes the importance of remembering and helping those who are less fortunate. The President mentions the tradition of zakat-ul-fitr, where Muslim communities collect and distribute charity, and highlights his administration's efforts to support Muslims in fulfilling their charitable obligations throughout the year. He concludes by congratulating Muslims on this blessed day and wishing them Eid Mubarak.